'''Ambattur''' is a part of Chennai Corporation. Closer to [[Anna Nagar]], [[Padi]] and [[Avadi]], Ambattur is a fast developing residential locality and [[Information technology|IT]] hub of Chennai. It covers an area of 45&nbsp;km<U+00B2>.

==Etymology==
This place is one of 108 Shakthi Sthals in the country. The Amman (Durga) temple here is 51st in the order and therefore this place was called "aimbaththu Oram ur', meaning 51st place/Temple village in Tamil, which later transmuted as Ambattur. The Goddess is worshiped in the form of Vaishnavi.

